    <h3> Steffi </h3>
    <p> After a relaxed and accompanied night in Congo, I was drawn out of the camper very early. Why stay there when you already sleep directly on the beach and are awake at sunrise! </p>
    <p> The gentleman next to me was still asleep, so I sneaked out quietly out of the car and went down to the beach. Since the sun was still hidden behind the cliffs, it was first to be rolled up in training pants and walk through water channels to the other side so that you caught the really chic look. I guess I haven't had such a relaxed and nice morning for a long time. Have a nice sunrise, a deserted beach, the rushing of the waves and otherwise absolute calm ... what more you want (I) ??? </p>
    <p> After I just let myself fall into the sand and enjoyed the moment for some time, I was put on my feet again to walk a little on the beach and to capture the whole thing in a few pictures. In the meantime, the sun had also come around the cliffs and I slowly made my way back to the camper. </p>
    <p> After we had prepared everything for the departure, Basti began to put the rough plan for the day. </p>
