    <p> During this, I grabbed the camera again and took the recommended path from the guardian of the square to the beach. This was found quite quickly ... steps up on the hill, other side steps down and again arrived at a beautiful and above all, deserted beach. What a sight ... you could feel comfortable here! <br> I stood on the last stage, I just wanted to shoot my flip -flops into the corner to take the last step into the sand, then I saw the first jellyfish right in front of my nose. Ok ... So start flip -flops and go on. Better, because the beach was overlooked with jellyfish and since it all look the same for me, whether dangerous or not ... <br> But there were not only jellyfish to see there, but also really chic shells etc., which simply invited to take away. Really frustrating that you are not allowed to take them with you! </p>
    <p> I could have spent ages there, but the journey had to go on and so I hit the way back after 20 minutes and we stowed the rest in the car and drove off. </p>
