    <p> But it quickly became a lot more beautiful because I was looking for another beach on our tour today that should be very nice. There we took our first major break. The little bay with the name Mystery Bay is really fantastic. As stolen from a travel catalog. An older couple was swimming in the water. When we got closer they were just getting out. Otherwise there was no other human soul. The couple offered us to take a photo of us and gave us a few more tips where you can drive along. </p>
    <p> As soon as the two were out of view, a little battle started. We left our most important electronic devices in the shoes on the beach and started a small water battle. After just a few minutes we were wet to the bones, which absolutely didn't bother us in the beautiful weather. We were still rolating around for some time before we had to go on. We would have loved to stay there, but the toilets at the Campin Square were just for choking. </p>
    <p> I also wanted to go to Melbourne a little, because Steffi's Genick worried me a little because it just didn't seem to get better. </p>
    <p> I didn't drive 5 minutes on the Highway (Bundeststrasse in Germany). I just started an audio book and enjoyed the trip through apparently endless primeval forests. Berg up and mountain down. </p>
    <p> It really took a few hours and a tank stop in a small town with H&uuml;pschen marina before we arrived in Cann River. A small sleepy village. Unfortunately, the coordinates in the camping guide were again not acurate. After a short procedure, we stopped at a petrol station to ask for the way. We could help us and also told us that we had to pay seat fees in the opposite hotel. </p>
    <p> When we arrived at the campsite 10 minutes later, we also realized why. Except for a toilet house and an open kitchen, there wasn't much there. So we chose a place and finally wanted to look at the Cannen River. Unfortunately, this was a letdown because it did not lead a lot of water in High and could therefore be described with small stream. </p>
    <p> We decided to make ourselves comfortable and just enjoy the day. With the darkness, however, it became exciting again. When we both on the way from the bathroom back to the van, two pairs of furry eyes looked in the eucalyptus tree behind the car. At first we didn't know what kind of animals it was. So first exercise caution. The two did not make any institutions away from us. So we unanimously decided that Steffi quickly stowed the remaining little things in the car and I take care that these two fur balls do not get too close to us. </p>
    <p> They thought differently and walked across the square to the next camper with an unshakable serenity. After Steffi was in bed once, I wanted to quickly go to the toilet. On the way there I watched the two animals again. When I passed, I heard a lady explain in English that it was so -called " <a title="Deutsches Wiki zum Thema Ringatil Possum" href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ringelschwanz-Kletterbeutler" target="_blank"> Ringtail Possums </a> "Handle. Just as you spoke about these animals was clear that the two of them are not dangerous. So we both were able to fall asleep down. </p>
